main event: A pilot observed a brilliantly lighted object flying at high altitude and high speed in Greenland on November 25, 1951.
interesting points: The object was flying at approximately 25,000 feet at an estimated speed of 700-800 mph., The sighting occurred during a routine patrol flight., The pilot observed the object for about 2 minutes before it disappeared from view., This sighting was reported as the fourth in the past week in the Greenland area., The object maintained a constant course and speed throughout the observation.
sighted object: a brilliantly lighted object in the sky
